A 54-year-old businesswoman is admitted at the Kenyatta National Hospital, where she is receiving treatment for a bullet wound on her hand.Agatha Gicuku was caught up in a fire exchange between police and suspected criminals. She was shot in the right arm on Saturday night as police officers pursued criminals who had attacked a bar in Kamukunji, Nairobi. It was not immediately established whether Gicuku, who is reported to have been walking home at around 8.30pm, was shot by police or the fleeing criminals. Nairobi CID boss Ireri Kamwende said police have opened investigations. He said Gicuku is out of danger. Meanwhile, a police officer based at the Buruburu police station was arrested and locked up after he shot and killed a man on the Umoja estate on Saturday night.